President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of New York due to severe storms and flooding that occurred from March 13-15, 2010. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas, including Nassau, Orange, Richmond, Rockland, Suffolk, and Westchester counties. The funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures statewide. Albert Lewis has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.